empt to articulate a better, more sensitive, and ultimately more productive model for change—a model Galvan calls "institutional syncretism."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAcculturationzSenegalvCase studies. 0aLand tenurezSenegalzSine-SaloumxHistory. 0aSerer (African people)xGovernment relations. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aacademic.  aagriculture.  achange.  acolonial rulers.  acolonial.  acolonialism.  aecology.  aeconomics.  aecosystem.  aecosystems.  aenvironmentalism.  aenvironmentalist.  aland cultivation.  aland tenure.  aland use.  aproductive agriculture.  aregional.  arural community.  arural land.  arural society.  ascholarly.  asenegal.  asocial change.  asocial justice.  asocial studies.  asociety.  asustainability.  atransformation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023591540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092942540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520929425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520929425/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY